43class NonCopyable
44{
45 protected:
46 constexpr NonCopyable() = default;
47 ~NonCopyable() = default;
48
49 private:
50 NonCopyable(const NonCopyable &) = delete;
51 void operator=(const NonCopyable &) = delete;
52};

58template <typename T, size_t N>
59constexpr inline size_t ArraySize(T (&)[N])
60{
61 return N;
62}
63
64template <typename T>
65class WrappedArray final : angle::NonCopyable
66{
67 public:
68 template <size_t N>
69 constexpr WrappedArray(const T (&data)[N]) : mArray(&data[0]), mSize(N)
70 {}
71
72 constexpr WrappedArray() : mArray(nullptr), mSize(0) {}
73 constexpr WrappedArray(const T *data, size_t size) : mArray(data), mSize(size) {}
74
75 WrappedArray(WrappedArray &&other) : WrappedArray()
76 {
77 std::swap(mArray, other.mArray);
78 std::swap(mSize, other.mSize);
79 }
80
81 ~WrappedArray() {}
82
83 constexpr const T *get() const { return mArray; }
84 constexpr size_t size() const { return mSize; }
85
86 private:
87 const T *mArray;
88 size_t mSize;
89};

91template <typename T, unsigned int N>
92void SafeRelease(T (&resourceBlock)[N])
93{
94 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < N; i++)
95 {
96 SafeRelease(resourceBlock[i]);
97 }
98}
99
100template <typename T>
101void SafeRelease(T &resource)
102{
103 if (resource)
104 {
105 resource->Release();
106 resource = nullptr;
107 }
108}
109
110template <typename T>
111void SafeDelete(T *&resource)
112{
113 delete resource;
114 resource = nullptr;
115}
116
117template <typename T>
118void SafeDeleteContainer(T &resource)
119{
120 for (auto &element : resource)
121 {
122 SafeDelete(element);
123 }
124 resource.clear();
125}
126
127template <typename T>
128void SafeDeleteArray(T *&resource)
129{
130 delete[] resource;
131 resource = nullptr;
132}

134// Provide a less-than function for comparing structs
135// Note: struct memory must be initialized to zero, because of packing gaps
136template <typename T>
137inline bool StructLessThan(const T &a, const T &b)
138{
139 return (memcmp(&a, &b, sizeof(T)) < 0);
140}
141
142// Provide a less-than function for comparing structs
143// Note: struct memory must be initialized to zero, because of packing gaps
144template <typename T>
145inline bool StructEquals(const T &a, const T &b)
146{
147 return (memcmp(&a, &b, sizeof(T)) == 0);
148}
149
150template <typename T>
151inline void StructZero(T *obj)
152{
153 memset(obj, 0, sizeof(T));
154}
155
156template <typename T>
157inline bool IsMaskFlagSet(T mask, T flag)
158{
159 // Handles multibit flags as well
160 return (mask & flag) == flag;
161}
162
163inline const char *MakeStaticString(const std::string &str)
164{
165 // On the heap so that no destructor runs on application exit.
166 static std::set<std::string> *strings = new std::set<std::string>;
167 std::set<std::string>::iterator it = strings->find(str);
168 if (it != strings->end())
169 {
170 return it->c_str();
171 }
172
173 return strings->insert(str).first->c_str();
174}

182inline std::string Str(int i)
183{
184 std::stringstream strstr;
185 strstr << i;
186 return strstr.str();
187}

191template <typename T>
192std::string ToString(const T &value)
193{
194 std::ostringstream o;
195 o << value;
196 return o.str();
197}

199inline bool IsLittleEndian()
200{
201 constexpr uint32_t kEndiannessTest = 1;
202 const bool isLittleEndian = *reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(&kEndiannessTest) == 1;
203 return isLittleEndian;
204}

299// The below inlining code lifted from V8.
300#if defined(__clang__) || (defined(__GNUC__) && defined(__has_attribute))
301# define ANGLE_HAS_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE (__has_attribute(always_inline))
302# define ANGLE_HAS___FORCEINLINE 0
303#elif defined(_MSC_VER)
304# define ANGLE_HAS_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE 0
305# define ANGLE_HAS___FORCEINLINE 1
306#else
307# define ANGLE_HAS_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE 0
308# define ANGLE_HAS___FORCEINLINE 0
309#endif
310
311#if defined(NDEBUG) && ANGLE_HAS_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE
312# define ANGLE_INLINE inline __attribute__((always_inline))
313#elif defined(NDEBUG) && ANGLE_HAS___FORCEINLINE
314# define ANGLE_INLINE __forceinline
315#else
316# define ANGLE_INLINE inline
317#endif
318
319#if defined(__clang__) || (defined(__GNUC__) && defined(__has_attribute))
320# if __has_attribute(noinline)
321# define ANGLE_NOINLINE __attribute__((noinline))
322# else
323# define ANGLE_NOINLINE
324# endif
325#elif defined(_MSC_VER)
326# define ANGLE_NOINLINE __declspec(noinline)
327#else
328# define ANGLE_NOINLINE
329#endif
330
331#if defined(__clang__) || (defined(__GNUC__) && defined(__has_attribute))
332# if __has_attribute(format)
333# define ANGLE_FORMAT_PRINTF(fmt, args) __attribute__((format(__printf__, fmt, args)))
334# else
335# define ANGLE_FORMAT_PRINTF(fmt, args)
336# endif
337#else
338# define ANGLE_FORMAT_PRINTF(fmt, args)
339#endif
